Mens et Manus Linguistics 

Tutorial on how to build a syllabifier based on Sonority Sequencing principle

1. Link to CMU pronunciation dictionary- https://raw.githubusercontent.com/cmusphinx/cmudict/master/cmudict.dict

2. Phone set documentation- https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ARPABET

3. Follow the steps in the Jupyter notebook.

4. Try to tweak the definition of valid syllable by adding onset and coda constraints.

5. Try this parser with a new language and a new phone set (IPA).
